126.8	Abraham	Abraham	Abraham , Modern: , Tiberian: , Ashkenazi Avrohom or Avruhom, Arabic: â€Ž , Ge'ez: , Greek: , Russian: ), whose birth name was Abram, is the eponym of the Abrahamic religions, among which are Judaism, Christianity and Islam. According to both the Hebrew Bible and the Qur'an, through his sons Ishmael and Isaac, Abraham is the forefather of many tribes, namely the Ishmaelites, Israelites, Midianites and Edomites. Abraham was a descendant of Noah's son, Shem. Christians believe that Jesus was a descendant of Abraham through Isaac, and Muslims believe that Muhammad was a descendant of Abraham through Ishmael.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4f/Rembrandt_Harmensz._van_Rijn_035.jpg/250px-Rembrandt_Harmensz._van_Rijn_035.jpg
